posts.name: Erik
posts.cooked:
Background: We have a fairly small team who is new to Swerve and are struggling on the code side.  We have one student who knows Java and while I know Java, I have no experience with getting this going and am hoping YAGSL would help us bridge the gap. Students fundraised in the Spring for a Swerve config using WCP Swerve X Flipped, Krakens + Neos, Cancoders and a Pigeon 2 which is what we now have and are trying to code. Unfortunately didn’t raise enough for the second set of krakens to use the out of box CTRE configurator.

As we try to get our basic starter robot code deployed to the robot, we get an IllegalStateException error on com.revrobotics.spark.SparkBase.configure which is called from our SwerveSubsystem when instantiating a SwerveDrive.  We’ve tried to instantiate this SwerveDrive in simpler ways but it always seems to error out.

Our code is here.  It doesn’t do anything yet really…we are just getting started and its been a stumble.  Any help is appreciated.

GitHub - 8746Knights/Marshall Contribute to 8746Knights/Marshall development by creating an account on GitHub.

Contribute to 8746Knights/Marshall development by creating an account on GitHub.

posts.name: Erik
posts.cooked: Yes, we updated all the SparkMax firmware (and the Kraken & Cancoder).  We also set all CAN IDs which are playing nice and set accurately based on what you see in those config files. We also just updated tonight the REVlib to 2025.0.2 but that didn’t change anything.   I’ll look at the locations - but assume that won’t cause the exception we are seeing?
Did you update your SparkMAXs to 25.0.2? Which was released yesterday?

posts.name: Erik
posts.cooked: No, we updated REVlib when running into issues which went to 25.0.2, didn’t think about checking the SparkMaxes which is 25.0.1.  I’ll have the team do that today and report back.
Remember to factory reset them after updating!

posts.name: Erik
posts.cooked: Is factory reset the same as going to recovery mode and loading the latest?

posts.name: Erik
posts.cooked: Students did upgrade to 25.0.2 and have same errors / we will try factory reset via recovery mode
Could you put the full stack trace here so we can help further, a photo of your REV HW Client with all of your ids will he helpful too.
Can you please set your locations to the correct numbers, it should crash immediately if its 0 (or it will in the next update at least)

posts.cooked:
We still don’t have a factor set, but the latest code loads on the robot and joystick now moves the wheels (up on blocks).

Students pushed the latest code to our github and are trying to learn what to do next.
Do not set the factors, they are calculated but not to infinity this time! Your next steps should be the YAGSL youtube videos
